C

Cat - Class in SpeciesContainer
The Cat Class is for creating a Species of type Cat it inherits its methods from the abstract class Species which then becomes a pet.
Cat() - Constructor for class SpeciesContainer.Cat
The method Cat() initializes the Cat by creating a Cat of type Species in which its species name, weight and damage value are already preset.
checkValidName(ArrayList<Player>, String) - Method in class GUI.GUICreation
This method is used to check if a player name is a duplicate and to return a boolean value stating if they are.
checkValidPetName(ArrayList<String>, String, String, String) - Method in class GUI.GUICreation
This method is used to check if pet names are duplicates and to return a boolean value stating if they are.
createFood() - Method in class GUI.GUICreation
This Method is used to create a list of all types of Food
createSpecies() - Method in class GUI.GUICreation
This Method is used to create a list of all types of species
createToys() - Method in class GUI.GUICreation
This Method is used to create a list of all types of Toys
currentPlayer(ArrayList<Player>) - Method in class GUI.GUIMain
This method is used to set the playerList.
